Go-NoGo Task.Description: The Go-NoGo Task measures ability to inhibit a motor response

ExperimentName.Description: Name of the experiment used to generate the data file

DataFile.Basename.Description: basename of data output from E-prime. Format is ExperimentName-Subject-Session

ExperimentVersion.Description: Version of the experiment used to generate the data file

Group.Description: Group number. As part of this experiment, no Group is assigned at runtime, so defaults to 1

RandomSeed.Description: Auto-generated random seed used for randomization

RuntimeVersion.Description: E-run (E-prime application) version used to run experiment

RuntimeVersionExpected.Description: E-run (E-prime application) version expected to run experiment

SessionDate.Description: Date of experiment; based on the computer experiment is run from

SessionStartDateTimeUtc.Description: Date and time of experiment in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)

SessionTime.Description: Time of experiment; based on the computer experiment is run from

Block.Description: Block number. Equal to BlockList if experiment only contained task blocks (true when ExperimentName = Go No-Go Zoo_pseudorand)

Prac.Description: Prac ID being run. ID corresponds to a practice block procedure. Only 1 practice block procedure in this experiment

Prac.Cycle.Description: Cycle number of Prac list (1 cycle = 1 PracticeProc). Task was programmed for 1 cycle

Prac.Sample.Description: Order Prac sample (1 practice procedure block) was presented within Prac. Only 1 practice procedure block is presented

Procedure[Block].Description: Name of Procedure at the block level

Levels.PracticeProc: A procedure with Welcome2 screen, OrangFam1 screen, PracticeReady screen, Practice (a list of 12 gonogo samples), PracticeOut screen, ZooMap1 screen

Levels.Prac: A list that contains 1 practice procedure block (PracticeProc)

Trial.Description: Trial number within the corresponding Procedure[Block] (e.g., 1 = first trial presented during the corresponding task block). Range: 1-12

imagecode.Description: number associated with image file presented (s1)

Practice.Description: ID of sample (image) from Practice (range: 1-12). Will be equal to Practice.Sample if sample selection was not randomized

Practice.Cycle.Description: Cycle number of Practice list (1 cycle = 12 samples). Task was programmed for 1 cycle

Practice.Sample.Description: Order sample (image) was presented within Practice (range: 1-12). For example, 1 = first sample presented, 5 = fifth sample presented.

Procedure[Trial].Description: Name of procedure at the trial level

Levels.TrialProc: Procedure containing a fixation (300ms), stimulus screen presenting s1 (750ms), and response screen (500ms)

Respond.ACC.Description: Indicates whether Respond.RESP was equal to Respond.CRESP

Respond.CRESP.Description: Correct response for 'Respond' screen. The same as Stim.CRESP

Respond.RESP.Description: Actual response made during response screen (blank screen that follows s1 presentation)

Respond.RT.Description: Timestamp of the Respond.RESP from the time that response screen was displayed (750ms after presentation of s1). Value of 0 indicates no response occured during response screen

Respond.RTTime.Description: Timestamp of the response from the time that the experiment started

s1.Description: name of bitmap image file displayed. These image files contain animal pictures

Stim.ACC.Description: Indicates whether Stim.RESP was equal to Stim.CRESP

Stim.RESP.Description: Actual response made during presentation of Stim screen (screen presenting s1)

Stim.RT.Description: Timestamp of the Stim.RESP from the time that the stimulus (s1) was displayed (reaction time to stimulus). Value of 0 indicates no response occured during stimulus presentation

Stim.RTTime.Description: Timestamp of the response from the time that the experiment started

Target.Description: Stimulus image presented. Equal to s1
